ed? How did Berkeley benefit from the 1906 earthquake that destroyed much of San Francisco? What differentiated Holy Hill from Nut Hill? Berkeley: A City in History offers a delightful sense of place to anyone who has lived in, worked in, or traveled through this unique city.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / West (AK, CA, CO, HI, ID, MT, NV, UT, WY).2bisacsh  a1906 earthquake.  aatomic age.  aberkeley california.  ablue-collar residents.  acalifornia history.  acollege textbook.  adepression era.  agreat earthquake.  ahigher education.  aholy hill.  alarger historical themes.  anatural disasters.  anut hill.  aocean view.  arailroad age.  asan francisco.  ashellmounds.  asixties.  auniversities.  aworld war ii shipyards.  aww ii.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052025307040uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093425240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520934252423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520934252/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY